{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775866592600,"sessionID":"ses_2861a84c3ffeB0FRMtscWRyHqZ","part":{"id":"prt_d79e5bb2b001VMjSs45NaJynN5","messageID":"msg_d79e5a6ce001Zn5Pblt6BSlL4B","sessionID":"ses_2861a84c3ffeB0FRMtscWRyHqZ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_e34cfb9396684895ab2b6470","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification — AR-019: CLI 二进制入口 (4 binaries)\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **Module:** `cmd`  \n6: **Language:** Go  \n7: **Size:** M  \n8: **Type:** New feature — CLI binaries for agentcube Kubernetes resources\n9: \n10: **Base Specs:** deployment/client-go.md\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements & Scenarios\n15: \n16: ### REQ-019.1: CLI Configuration Loading\n17: \n18: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a CLI configuration loader that supports kubeconfig file path flag (`--kubeconfig`) and `KUBECONFIG` environment variable. If neither is provided, the system SHALL use default path `~/.kube/config`. The system SHALL provide clear error messages for invalid or missing configuration.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: Load kubeconfig from flag\n21: - **GIVEN** user provides `--kubeconfig /path/to/config`\n22: - **WHEN** CLI initializes\n23: - **THEN** loads Kubernetes configuration from specified path\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Load kubeconfig from environment\n26: - **GIVEN** `KUBECONFIG` environment variable is set to `/path/to/config`\n27: - **WHEN** CLI initializes without `--kubeconfig` flag\n28: - **THEN** loads Kubernetes configuration from environment path\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Use default kubeconfig path\n31: - **GIVEN** no `--kubeconfig` flag and no `KUBECONFIG` environment variable\n32: - **WHEN** CLI initializes\n33: - **THEN** loads configuration from `~/.kube/config`\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Error on missing kubeconfig\n36: - **GIVEN** kubeconfig file does not exist\n37: - **WHEN** CLI attempts to load configuration\n38: - **THEN** returns error \"kubeconfig file not found: <path>\" and exits with code 1\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Error on invalid kubeconfig\n41: - **GIVEN** kubeconfig file has invalid YAML format\n42: - **WHEN** CLI attempts to load configuration\n43: - **THEN** returns error \"failed to parse kubeconfig: <detail>\" and exits with code 1\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Error on authentication failure\n46: - **GIVEN** kubeconfig has expired or invalid credentials\n47: - **WHEN** CLI attempts to connect to cluster\n48: - **THEN** returns error \"authentication failed: <detail>\" with suggestions to refresh credentials\n49: \n50: ---\n51: \n52: ### REQ-019.2: agent-runtime Subcommand\n53: \n54: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `agentcube agent-runtime` subcommand with operations: `list`, `get`, `create`, `delete`. The system SHALL support output formats: table (default), JSON (`-o json`), YAML (`-o yaml`).\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: List all AgentRuntimes\n57: - **GIVEN** cluster has AgentRuntime resources in multiple namespaces\n58: - **WHEN** user executes `agentcube agent-runtime list`\n59: - **THEN** displays table with columns: NAME, NAMESPACE, STATUS, AGE\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: List AgentRuntimes in specific namespace\n62: - **GIVEN** user specifies `-n <namespace>` flag\n63: - **WHEN** user executes `agentcube agent-runtime list -n default`\n64: - **THEN** displays only AgentRuntimes in specified namespace\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: Get AgentRuntime details as YAML\n67: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime named `my-runtime` exists in `default` namespace\n68: - **WHEN** user executes `agentcube agent-runtime get my-runtime -n default -o yaml`\n69: - **THEN** outputs full AgentRuntime resource as YAML\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: Get AgentRuntime details as JSON\n72: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime named `my-runtime` exists\n73: - **WHEN** user executes `agentcube agent-runtime get my-runtime -n default -o json`\n74: - **THEN** outputs full AgentRuntime resource as JSON\n75: \n76: #### Scenario: Create AgentRuntime from file\n77: - **GIVEN** a valid manifest file `runtime.yaml`\n78: - **WHEN** user executes `agentcube agent-runtime create -f runtime.yaml`\n79: - **THEN** creates AgentRuntime and outputs \"agentruntime/<name> created\"\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: Create AgentRuntime from stdin\n82: - **GIVEN** a valid manifest piped to stdin\n83: - **WHEN** user executes `agentcube agent-runtime create -f -`\n84: - **THEN** creates AgentRuntime from stdin content\n85: \n86: #### Scenario: Delete AgentRuntime\n87: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime named `my-runtime` exists\n88: - **WHEN** user executes `agentcube agent-runtime delete my-runtime -n default`\n89: - **THEN** deletes AgentRuntime and outputs \"agentruntime \"my-runtime\" deleted\"\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: Delete AgentRuntime with grace period\n92: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime named `my-runtime` exists\n93: - **WHEN** user executes `agentcube agent-runtime delete my-runtime -n default --grace-period=30`\n94: - **THEN** deletes AgentRuntime with 30 second grace period\n95: \n96: #### Scenario: Force delete AgentRuntime\n97: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime that is stuck in terminating state\n98: - **WHEN** user executes `agentcube agent-runtime delete my-runtime -n default --force`\n99: - **THEN** immediately removes finalizers and deletes AgentRuntime\n100: \n101: #### Scenario: Get non-existent AgentRuntime\n102: - **GIVEN** no AgentRuntime named `missing` exists\n103: - **WHEN** user executes `agentcube agent-runtime get missing -n default`\n104: - **THEN** returns error \"agentruntime.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh \"missing\" not found\" with exit code 1\n105: \n106: ---\n107: \n108: ### REQ-019.3: code-interpreter Subcommand\n109: \n110: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `agentcube code-interpreter` subcommand with operations: `list`, `get`, `create`, `delete`. The system SHALL support same output formats and flags as agent-runtime subcommand.\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: List all CodeInterpreters\n113: - **GIVEN** cluster has CodeInterpreter resources\n114: - **WHEN** user executes `agentcube code-interpreter list`\n115: - **THEN** displays table with columns: NAME, NAMESPACE, STATUS, AGE\n116: \n117: #### Scenario: Get CodeInterpreter details\n118: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter named `my-interpreter` exists\n119: - **WHEN** user executes `agentcube code-interpreter get my-interpreter -n default`\n120: - **THEN** outputs CodeInterpreter details in specified format\n121: \n122: #### Scenario: Create CodeInterpreter from file\n123: - **GIVEN** a valid manifest file `interpreter.yaml`\n124: - **WHEN** user executes `agentcube code-interpreter create -f interpreter.yaml`\n125: - **THEN** creates CodeInterpreter and outputs \"codeinterpreter/<name> created\"\n126: \n127: #### Scenario: Delete CodeInterpreter\n128: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter named `my-interpreter` exists\n129: - **WHEN** user executes `agentcube code-interpreter delete my-interpreter -n default`\n130: - **THEN** deletes CodeInterpreter and outputs \"codeinterpreter \"my-interpreter\" deleted\"\n131: \n132: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter not found\n133: - **GIVEN** no CodeInterpreter named `missing` exists\n134: - **WHEN** user executes `agentcube code-interpreter get missing -n default`\n135: - **THEN** returns error with exit code 1\n136: \n137: ---\n138: \n139: ### REQ-019.4: CLI Binary Structure\n140: \n141: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide 4 binary entry points:\n142: 1. `agentcube` - Main CLI tool with all subcommands\n143: 2. `agentcube-agent-runtime` - Dedicated tool for AgentRuntime management\n144: 3. `agentcube-code-interpreter` - Dedicated tool for CodeInterpreter management\n145: 4. `agentcube-admin` - Admin tool for cluster-level operations\n146: \n147: #### Scenario: Main agentcube binary\n148: - **GIVEN** user runs `agentcube --help`\n149: - **WHEN** binary executes\n150: - **THEN** displays help with subcommands: `agent-runtime`, `code-interpreter`, `admin`\n151: \n152: #### Scenario: Dedicated agent-runtime binary\n153: - **GIVEN** user runs `agentcube-agent-runtime --help`\n154: - **WHEN** binary executes\n155: - **THEN** displays help with subcommands: `list`, `get`, `create`, `delete`\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: Dedicated code-interpreter binary\n158: - **GIVEN** user runs `agentcube-code-interpreter --help`\n159: - **WHEN** binary executes\n160: - **THEN** displays help with subcommands: `list`, `get`, `create`, `delete`\n161: \n162: #### Scenario: Admin binary for cluster operations\n163: - **GIVEN** user runs `agentcube-admin --help`\n164: - **WHEN** binary executes\n165: - **THEN** displays help with cluster-level admin commands\n166: \n167: ---\n168: \n169: ### REQ-019.5: Connection Error Handling\n170: \n171: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide clear error messages for connection failures, including timeout details and troubleshooting suggestions.\n172: \n173: #### Scenario: Cluster unreachable\n174: - **GIVEN** Kubernetes API server is not reachable\n175: - **WHEN** CLI attempts to connect\n176: - **THEN** returns error \"unable to connect to cluster: connection timed out (server: <host>)\" with suggestion to check network/firewall\n177: \n178: #### Scenario: Connection timeout\n179: - **GIVEN** cluster responds slowly or network is congested\n180: - **WHEN** request exceeds timeout threshold\n181: - **THEN** returns error \"request timed out after <duration>s\" with suggestion to use `--request-timeout` flag\n182: \n183: #### Scenario: Namespace not found\n184: - **GIVEN** user specifies non-existent namespace\n185: - **WHEN** CLI attempts to list resources\n186: - **THEN** returns error \"namespace \"<name>\" not found\" with exit code 1\n187: \n188: ---\n189: \n190: ### REQ-019.6: Output Formatting\n191: \n192: **Requirement:** The system SHALL support multiple output formats via `-o` flag: `table` (default), `json`, `yaml`, `wide`, `name`.\n193: \n194: #### Scenario: Table output (default)\n195: - **GIVEN** resources exist\n196: - **WHEN** user executes list command without `-o` flag\n197: - **THEN** displays formatted table with headers\n198: \n199: #### Scenario: JSON output\n200: - **GIVEN** resource exists\n201: - **WHEN** user executes get command with `-o json`\n202: - **THEN** outputs resource as JSON\n203: \n204: #### Scenario: YAML output\n205: - **GIVEN** resource exists\n206: - **WHEN** user executes get command with `-o yaml`\n207: - **THEN** outputs resource as YAML\n208: \n209: #### Scenario: Wide output\n210: - **GIVEN** resources exist\n211: - **WHEN** user executes list command with `-o wide`\n212: - **THEN** displays table with additional columns (e.g., labels, annotations)\n213: \n214: #### Scenario: Name output\n215: - **GIVEN** resources exist\n216: - **WHEN** user executes list command with `-o name`\n217: - **THEN** outputs only resource names, one per line\n218: \n219: ---\n220: \n221: ## Data Types\n222: \n223: ```go\n224: // CLIConfig holds CLI configuration\n225: type CLIConfig struct {\n226:     Kubeconfig     string\n227:     Namespace      string\n228:     OutputFormat   string\n229:     RequestTimeout time.Duration\n230: }\n231: \n232: // Command represents a CLI command interface\n233: type Command interface {\n234:     Execute() error\n235: }\n236: \n237: // AgentRuntimeCommand handles agent-runtime operations\n238: type AgentRuntimeCommand struct {\n239:     Operation string // list, get, create, delete\n240:     Name      string\n241:     Namespace string\n242:     File      string\n243:     Force     bool\n244:     GracePeriod int\n245: }\n246: \n247: // CodeInterpreterCommand handles code-interpreter operations\n248: type CodeInterpreterCommand struct {\n249:     Operation string\n250:     Name      string\n251:     Namespace string\n252:     File      string\n253:     Force     bool\n254:     GracePeriod int\n255: }\n256: ```\n257: \n258: ---\n259: \n260: ## Command-Line Flags\n261: \n262: | Flag | Binary | Description | Default |\n263: |------|--------|-------------|---------|\n264: | `--kubeconfig` | all | Path to kubeconfig file | `$KUBECONFIG` or `~/.kube/config` |\n265: | `-n, --namespace` | all | Target namespace | `default` |\n266: | `-o, --output` | all | Output format (table, json, yaml, wide, name) | `table` |\n267: | `--request-timeout` | all | Request timeout duration | `30s` |\n268: | `-f, --filename` | create | Manifest file path or `-` for stdin | - |\n269: | `--force` | delete | Force delete (remove finalizers) | `false` |\n270: | `--grace-period` | delete | Grace period in seconds | default from API |\n271: \n272: ---\n273: \n274: ## Environment Variables\n275: \n276: | Variable | Description | Default |\n277: |----------|-------------|---------|\n278: | `KUBECONFIG` | Path to kubeconfig file | `~/.kube/config` |\n279: | `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | Default namespace | `default` |\n280: | `AGENTCUBE_OUTPUT` | Default output format | `table` |\n281: \n282: ---\n283: \n284: ## File Structure\n285: \n286: ```\n287: cmd/\n288: ├── agentcube/\n289: │   └── main.go           # Main CLI entry point\n290: ├── agentcube-agent-runtime/\n291: │   └── main.go           # AgentRuntime dedicated binary\n292: ├── agentcube-code-interpreter/\n293: │   └── main.go           # CodeInterpreter dedicated binary\n294: ├── agentcube-admin/\n295: │   └── main.go           # Admin operations binary\n296: └── cli/\n297:     ├── config.go         # Configuration loading\n298:     ├── output.go         # Output formatters\n299:     ├── agentruntime/\n300:     │   ├── list.go\n301:     │   ├── get.go\n302:     │   ├── create.go\n303:     │   └── delete.go\n304:     └── codeinterpreter/\n305:         ├── list.go\n306:         ├── get.go\n307:         ├── create.go\n308:         └── delete.go\n309: ```\n310: \n311: ---\n312: \n313: ## Dependencies\n314: \n315: | Package | Purpose |\n316: |---------|---------|\n317: | `github.com/spf13/cobra` | CLI framework |\n318: | `k8s.io/client-go` | Kubernetes client |\n319: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | Kubernetes API types |\n320: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime/serializer` | JSON/YAML encoding |\n321: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Generated client for agentcube APIs |\n322: \n323: ---\n324: \n325: ## Acceptance Checklist\n326: \n327: - [ ] `cmd/agentcube/main.go` — Main CLI entry point with cobra\n328: - [ ] `cmd/agentcube-agent-runtime/main.go` — Dedicated binary\n329: - [ ] `cmd/agentcube-code-interpreter/main.go` — Dedicated binary\n330: - [ ] `cmd/agentcube-admin/main.go` — Admin binary\n331: - [ ] `cmd/cli/config.go` — Configuration loading with env support\n332: - [ ] `cmd/cli/output.go` — Output formatters (table, json, yaml, wide, name)\n333: - [ ] `cmd/cli/agentruntime/*.go` — AgentRuntime commands\n334: - [ ] `cmd/cli/codeinterpreter/*.go` — CodeInterpreter commands\n335: - [ ] All flags and environment variables supported\n336: - [ ] Error messages are clear and actionable\n337: - [ ] Exit codes are correct (0 for success, 1 for errors)\n338: - [ ] Code coverage >= 80%\n\n(End of file - total 338 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification — AR-019: CLI 二进制入口 (4 binaries)\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `cmd`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n**Type:** New feature — CLI binaries for agentcube Kubernetes resources\n\n**Base Specs:** deployment/client-go.md\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-019.1: CLI Configuration Loading\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a CLI configuration loader that supports kubeconfig file path flag (`--kubeconfig`) and `KUBECONFIG` environment variable. If neither is provided, the system SHALL use default path `~/.kube/config`. The system SHALL provide clear error messages for invalid or missing configuration.\n\n#### Scenario: Load kubeconfig from flag","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775866592588,"end":1775866592597}}}}
