{"type":"text","timestamp":1775866606917,"sessionID":"ses_2861a84c3ffeB0FRMtscWRyHqZ","part":{"id":"prt_d79e5eb68001J7QD9bUTwIhU6t","messageID":"msg_d79e5e127001amBfqmPdwwyKnA","sessionID":"ses_2861a84c3ffeB0FRMtscWRyHqZ","type":"text","text":"Now I have the context. The existing `cli-toolkit/spec.md` contains the full specification. Based on the `.sdd_prompt.md` task description, I need to write a **delta-spec.md** specifically for **AR-021 — CLI build 命令** that focuses on the changes/differences needed.\n\nLooking at the base spec, the build command requirements are already partially defined in section \"Requirement: `build` command\" (lines 40-57). The delta-spec should capture what needs to be added or changed from the base spec to fully implement the build command.\n\nLet me write the delta-spec.md for AR-021:","time":{"start":1775866606914,"end":1775866606914}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775866668390,"sessionID":"ses_2861a84c3ffeB0FRMtscWRyHqZ","part":{"id":"prt_d79e5f544001FvTsZ1ncfh4kNB","messageID":"msg_d79e5e127001amBfqmPdwwyKnA","sessionID":"ses_2861a84c3ffeB0FRMtscWRyHqZ","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_8f0d424a751d4d8694ecc583","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec-ar-021.md","content":"# Delta Specification — AR-021: CLI build 命令\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Type:** Implementation of build command for container image building\n\n**Base Specs:** cli-toolkit/design.md, cli-toolkit/spec.md\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-021.1: Build Command CLI Interface\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL implement the `build` Typer subcommand with options for workspace path, proxy configuration, cloud provider selection, output path, and verbose logging.\n\n#### Scenario: Build command registration\n- **GIVEN** the Typer app is initialized\n- **WHEN** the CLI loads\n- **THEN** the `build` subcommand SHALL be registered as `agentcube build`\n\n#### Scenario: Default workspace resolution\n- **GIVEN** user runs `agentcube build` without `-f` flag\n- **WHEN** the command executes\n- **THEN** workspace SHALL resolve to current directory `\".\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Custom workspace path\n- **GIVEN** user specifies `-f /path/to/workspace`\n- **WHEN** the command executes\n- **THEN** workspace SHALL resolve to the provided absolute or relative path\n\n#### Scenario: Proxy configuration via flag\n- **GIVEN** user specifies `-p http://proxy:port` or `--proxy http://proxy:port`\n- **WHEN** the command executes\n- **THEN** proxy SHALL be passed to build options for dependency resolution\n\n#### Scenario: Cloud provider selection\n- **GIVEN** user specifies `--cloud-provider huawei`\n- **WHEN** the command executes\n- **THEN** cloud provider SHALL override default build mode to `cloud`\n\n#### Scenario: Output path for build artifacts\n- **GIVEN** user specifies `--output /path/to/output`\n- **WHEN** the command completes\n- **THEN** build artifacts SHALL be copied or linked to the output path\n\n#### Scenario: Command-level verbose logging\n- **GIVEN** user specifies `--verbose` on build command\n- **WHEN** the command executes\n- **THEN** logging level SHALL be DEBUG for build operation only\n\n---\n\n### REQ-021.2: BuildRuntime Integration\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL instantiate `BuildRuntime` with verbose flag and invoke `build()` method with workspace path and options.\n\n#### Scenario: BuildRuntime instantiation\n- **GIVEN** build command is invoked\n- **WHEN** command handler runs\n- **THEN** `BuildRuntime(verbose=verbose)` SHALL be instantiated\n\n#### Scenario: Pass options to BuildRuntime.build\n- **GIVEN** CLI options are parsed\n- **WHEN** `BuildRuntime.build()` is called\n- **THEN** options dict SHALL include: `proxy`, `cloud_provider`, `output`, and any metadata overrides\n\n#### Scenario: Handle BuildRuntime exceptions\n- **GIVEN** `BuildRuntime.build()` raises an exception\n- **WHEN** exception is caught\n- **THEN** `_handle_error(e, \"build\", verbose)` SHALL be invoked\n\n#### Scenario: Display build success\n- **GIVEN** build completes successfully\n- **WHEN** `BuildRuntime.build()` returns result dict\n- **THEN** CLI SHALL print success message with image name, tag, and build time using Rich formatting\n\n---\n\n### REQ-021.3: Build Mode Resolution\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL determine build mode (local vs cloud) from metadata, with CLI `--cloud-provider` flag taking precedence.\n\n#### Scenario: Default to local build\n- **GIVEN** metadata has `build_mode: local` or no build_mode specified\n- **WHEN** `--cloud-provider` is not provided\n- **THEN** build mode SHALL be `local`\n\n#### Scenario: Cloud provider overrides to cloud mode\n- **GIVEN** user specifies `--cloud-provider huawei`\n- **WHEN** build mode is resolved\n- **THEN** build mode SHALL be `cloud` regardless of metadata\n\n#### Scenario: Cloud mode requires cloud provider\n- **GIVEN** metadata has `build_mode: cloud`\n- **WHEN** no `--cloud-provider` is specified\n- **THEN** system SHALL raise error requiring cloud provider name\n\n---\n\n### REQ-021.4: Local Docker Build Flow\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL execute local Docker build using `DockerService` when build mode is `local`.\n\n#### Scenario: Docker availability check\n- **GIVEN** build mode is `local`\n- **WHEN** build starts\n- **THEN** `DockerService.check_docker_available()` SHALL be called first\n\n#### Scenario: Docker not available error\n- **GIVEN** Docker daemon is not running\n- **WHEN** `check_docker_available()` fails\n- **THEN** `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")` SHALL be raised\n\n#### Scenario: Build image with DockerService\n- **GIVEN** Docker is available\n- **WHEN** local build proceeds\n- **THEN** `DockerService.build_image()` SHALL be called with:\n  - `dockerfile_path`: workspace/Dockerfile\n  - `context_path`: workspace\n  - `image_name`: `{agent_name}`\n  - `tag`: `{version}` or `latest`\n  - `build_args`: proxy settings if provided\n\n#### Scenario: Image tagging convention\n- **GIVEN** metadata version is `1.2.3`\n- **WHEN** image is built\n- **THEN** image tag SHALL be `{agent_name}:1.2.3`\n\n#### Scenario: Fallback tag when no version\n- **GIVEN** metadata has no version\n- **WHEN** image is built\n- **THEN** image tag SHALL default to `{agent_name}:latest`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-021.5: Version Increment Logic\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL increment version before local build and revert on failure.\n\n#### Scenario: Patch version increment\n- **GIVEN** current version is `1.2.3`\n- **WHEN** build starts\n- **THEN** version SHALL become `1.2.4` before build\n\n#### Scenario: Minor version increment\n- **GIVEN** current version is `1.2.0` and user requests minor bump\n- **WHEN** build starts\n- **THEN** version SHALL become `1.3.0`\n\n#### Scenario: Major version increment\n- **GIVEN** current version is `1.0.0` and user requests major bump\n- **WHEN** build starts\n- **THEN** version SHALL become `2.0.0`\n\n#### Scenario: Pre-release version handling\n- **GIVEN** current version is `1.0.0-alpha.1`\n- **WHEN** build starts\n- **THEN** version SHALL increment pre-release to `1.0.0-alpha.2`\n\n#### Scenario: Version revert on build failure\n- **GIVEN** build fails after version increment\n- **WHEN** error is caught\n- **THEN** metadata version SHALL be reverted to original value\n\n#### Scenario: Version string fallback\n- **GIVEN** version is not semver format (e.g., `v1.0`)\n- **WHEN** increment is attempted\n- **THEN** system SHALL append `.1` (e.g., `v1.0.1`) or use `{version}-1` fallback\n\n---\n\n### REQ-021.6: Cloud Build Flow\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL trigger cloud build when build mode is `cloud` and cloud provider is specified.\n\n#### Scenario: Cloud build prerequisite validation\n- **GIVEN** build mode is `cloud`\n- **WHEN** build starts\n- **THEN** system SHALL validate cloud provider credentials/configuration\n\n#### Scenario: Huawei cloud provider\n- **GIVEN** `--cloud-provider huawei`\n- **WHEN** cloud build is triggered\n- **THEN** system SHALL use Huawei Cloud Container Registry API\n\n#### Scenario: Cloud provider not supported\n- **GIVEN** `--cloud-provider unknown-provider`\n- **WHEN** build starts\n- **THEN** system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"Unsupported cloud provider: unknown-provider\")`\n\n#### Scenario: Cloud build status polling\n- **GIVEN** cloud build is triggered\n- **WHEN** build is in progress\n- **THEN** system SHALL poll build status with progress indicator\n\n#### Scenario: Cloud build timeout\n- **GIVEN** cloud build exceeds timeout (default 600s)\n- **WHEN** polling continues\n- **THEN** system SHALL raise `TimeoutError(\"Cloud build exceeded timeout\")`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-021.7: Build Validation Prerequisites\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL validate workspace prerequisites before build.\n\n#### Scenario: Dockerfile existence check\n- **GIVEN** build is about to start\n- **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._validate_build_prerequisites()` runs\n- **THEN** system SHALL check for Dockerfile in workspace\n\n#### Scenario: Missing Dockerfile\n- **GIVEN** no Dockerfile exists in workspace\n- **WHEN** validation runs\n- **THEN** system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"Dockerfile not found in workspace\")`\n\n#### Scenario: Metadata validation\n- **GIVEN** build is about to start\n- **WHEN** prerequisites are validated\n- **THEN** system SHALL verify `agent_metadata.yaml` exists and is valid\n\n#### Scenario: Image name validation\n- **GIVEN** agent_name contains invalid characters\n- **WHEN** build starts\n- **THEN** system SHALL sanitize or reject invalid image names per Docker naming rules\n\n---\n\n### REQ-021.8: Build Output and Reporting\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL report build results with image details, build time, and next steps.\n\n#### Scenario: Build success output\n- **GIVEN** build completes successfully\n- **WHEN** result is returned\n- **THEN** CLI SHALL print:\n  ```\n  ✓ Build completed successfully\n  Image: {image_name}:{tag}\n  Image ID: {image_id}\n  Size: {image_size}\n  Build time: {build_time}s\n  ```\n\n#### Scenario: Build result metadata update\n- **GIVEN** build succeeds\n- **WHEN** `_update_build_metadata()` runs\n- **THEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` SHALL be updated with image info (name, tag, id, size)\n\n#### Scenario: Verbose build logs\n- **GIVEN** `--verbose` is true\n- **WHEN** build runs\n- **THEN** Docker build logs SHALL be streamed to console\n\n#### Scenario: Next step guidance\n- **GIVEN** build succeeds\n- **WHEN** output is printed\n- **THEN** CLI SHALL suggest next command: `agentcube publish` with appropriate flags\n\n---\n\n### REQ-021.9: Proxy Configuration\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL support proxy configuration for dependency resolution during build.\n\n#### Scenario: Proxy via CLI flag\n- **GIVEN** user specifies `-p http://proxy:port`\n- **WHEN** build runs\n- **THEN** proxy SHALL be set as `build_arg` for Docker build\n\n#### Scenario: Proxy environment variable fallback\n- **GIVEN** no `-p` flag but `HTTP_PROXY` env var is set\n- **WHEN** build runs\n- **THEN** proxy SHALL be read from environment\n\n#### Scenario: Proxy for pip installs\n- **GIVEN** Python workspace with requirements.txt\n- **WHEN** build processes dependencies\n- **THEN** pip install SHALL use `--proxy` flag if proxy is configured\n\n#### Scenario: Proxy for maven builds\n- **GIVEN** Java workspace with pom.xml\n- **WHEN** build processes dependencies\n- **THEN** maven settings.xml SHALL include proxy configuration\n\n---\n\n## Data Types\n\n```python\n# Build command options\nclass BuildOptions(TypedDict, total=False):\n    workspace: str\n    proxy: Optional[str]\n    cloud_provider: Optional[str]\n    output: Optional[str]\n    verbose: bool\n\n# Build result structure\nclass BuildResult(TypedDict):\n    image_name: str\n    image_tag: str\n    image_id: str\n    image_size: str\n    build_time: str\n    build_mode: str\n    cloud_provider: Optional[str]\n```\n\n---\n\n## CLI Flags Summary\n\n| Flag | Short | Type | Default | Description |\n|------|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--workspace` | `-f` | str | `\".\"` | Path to agent workspace |\n| `--proxy` | `-p` | Optional[str] | None | Proxy URL for dependencies |\n| `--cloud-provider` | - | Optional[str] | None | Cloud provider name (huawei, etc.) |\n| `--output` | - | Optional[str] | None | Output path for artifacts |\n| `--verbose` | - | bool | False | Enable detailed logging |\n\n---\n\n## Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Description | Default |\n|----------|-------------|---------|\n| `HTTP_PROXY` | HTTP proxy for builds | - |\n| `HTTPS_PROXY` | HTTPS proxy for builds | - |\n| `DOCKER_HOST` | Docker daemon socket | system default |\n\n---\n\n## Error Codes\n\n| Error | Exit Code | Message |\n|-------|-----------|---------|\n| Docker unavailable | 1 | \"Docker is not available or not running\" |\n| Missing Dockerfile | 1 | \"Dockerfile not found in workspace\" |\n| Invalid cloud provider | 1 | \"Unsupported cloud provider: {name}\" |\n| Build failure | 1 | \"Build failed: {detail}\" |\n| Cloud build timeout | 1 | \"Cloud build exceeded timeout ({duration}s)\" |\n| Version increment failure | 1 | \"Failed to increment version: {detail}\" |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `typer[all]` | >=0.9.0 | CLI framework |\n| `pydantic` | >=2.0.0 | Data validation |\n| `docker` | >=6.0.0 | Docker SDK |\n| `rich` | >=13.0.0 | Output formatting |\n| `semver` | >=3.0.0 | Version parsing |\n| `pyyaml` | >=6.0 | Metadata handling |\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Checklist\n\n- [ ] `agentcube/cli/main.py` — build command registered with Typer\n- [ ] `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` — BuildRuntime class implemented\n- [ ] `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` — DockerService for local builds\n- [ ] `agentcube/services/cloud_providers/` — Cloud provider implementations\n- [ ] Version increment logic with rollback on failure\n- [ ] Proxy configuration via flag and environment\n- [ ] Build prerequisites validation (Dockerfile, metadata)\n- [ ] Success/failure output with Rich formatting\n- [ ] Verbose mode streams build logs\n- [ ] Error handling with appropriate exit codes\n- [ ] Next step guidance after successful build\n- [ ] Code coverage >= 80% for build path\n\n---\n\n## Open Questions\n\n1. Should build command support `--tag` override for custom image tags?\n2. Should multi-platform builds (`--platform`) be supported in initial release?\n3. Should build cache options (`--no-cache`, `--cache-from`) be exposed?\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec-ar-021.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec-ar-021.md","time":{"start":1775866668376,"end":1775866668386}}}}
